quality tests, though an independent monitoring groupclassifiedthe health risks as being in a murky \\\"gray zone\\\" based on samples taken around the same time.\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 747, \"end\": 752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.99999727783695, \"rank\": 2.7221705738310776e-06, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the water-quality tests\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 794}, {\"ngram\": \"a murky \\\"gray zone\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 891}, {\"ngram\": \"samples\", \"from\": 902, \"to\": 909}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris wanted to prove that its years-long gamble on the river has paid off, and today, the city and the athletes are flush with victory (and hopefully notE.\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 1094, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 938, \"end\": 943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5840203743392823e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its years-long gamble\", \"from\": 965, \"to\": 986}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 990, \"to\": 999}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1033}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1050}, {\"ngram\": \"victory\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1073}, {\"ngram\": \"hopefully notE.\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1094}]}, {\"sentence\": \"coli).\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"coli\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1099}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The problem that the city faces-the very old, very tricky, very ongoing job of wrangling sewage-is not a uniquely Parisian challenge: Systems that dump waste into the river during heavy rain are common in theUnited States, theUnited Kingdom, and beyond.\", \"from\": 1105, \"to\": 1358, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The problem\", \"from\": 1105, \"to\": 1116}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1130}, {\"ngram\": \"the very old, very tricky, very ongoing job\", \"from\": 1137, \"to\": 1180}, {\"ngram\": \"wrangling sewage\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1200}, {\"ngram\": \"a uniquely Parisian challenge\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1237}, {\"ngram\": \"Systems\", \"from\": 1239, \"to\": 1246}, {\"ngram\": \"waste\", \"from\": 1257, \"to\": 1262}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1277}, {\"ngram\": \"heavy rain\", \"from\": 1285, \"to\": 1295}, {\"ngram\": \"theUnited States\", \"from\": 1310, \"to\": 1326}, {\"ngram\": \"theUnited Kingdom\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1345}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Paris happens to be a place that recently made particularly loud public promises about curbing this type of pollution.\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1363, \"end\": 1368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5840203743392823e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a place\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1390}, {\"ngram\": \"particularly loud public promises\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1443}, {\"ngram\": \"this type\", \"from\": 1458, \"to\": 1467}, {\"ngram\": \"pollution\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1480}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The city managed to fulfill those promises, and proved that even a famously dirty river can be made swimmable-just not necessarily on any one particular day.\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1639, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The city\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1490}, {\"ngram\": \"those promises\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1524}, {\"ngram\": \"even a famously dirty river\", \"from\": 1542, \"to\": 1569