6, \"to\": 1978}, {\"ngram\": \"sewage\", \"from\": 1994, \"to\": 2000}, {\"ngram\": \"garbage\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2025}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The waters must also meet particular limits forE.\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2076, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The waters\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2037}, {\"ngram\": \"particular limits\", \"from\": 2053, \"to\": 2070}]}, {\"sentence\": \"coliandEnterococcus, a genus of bacteria that proliferates in animals' intestines and serves asa proxyfor disease-causing bacteria that travel in feces.\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2229, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"coliandEnterococcus\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2096}, {\"ngram\": \"a genus\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2105}, {\"ngram\": \"bacteria\", \"from\": 2109, \"to\": 2117}, {\"ngram\": \"animals' intestines\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2158}, {\"ngram\": \"asa\", \"from\": 2170, \"to\": 2173}, {\"ngram\": \"disease-causing bacteria\", \"from\": 2183, \"to\": 2207}, {\"ngram\": \"feces\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2228}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some samples from the Seinefailed to meet these standards-whichexceed the limits recommendedby the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency-duringtests last monthafter heavy rains,andsome samples collected this weekrevealedE.\", \"from\": 2230, \"to\": 2451, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Some samples\", \"from\": 2230, \"to\": 2242}, {\"ngram\": \"the Seinefailed\", \"from\": 2248, \"to\": 2263}, {\"ngram\": \"these standards\", \"from\": 2272, \"to\": 2287}, {\"ngram\": \"the limits\", \"from\": 2300, \"to\": 2310}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency-duringtests\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2377}, {\"ngram\": \"heavy rains\", \"from\": 2394, \"to\": 2405}, {\"ngram\": \"andsome samples\", \"from\": 2406, \"to\": 2421}, {\"ngram\": \"this weekrevealedE.\", \"from\": 2432, \"to\": 2451}]}, {\"sentence\": \"colilevels that were unacceptably high following a downpour that made for asoggy opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 2452, \"to\": 2550, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"colilevels\", \"from\": 2452, \"to\": 2462}, {\"ngram\": \"a downpour\", \"from\": 2501, \"to\": 2511}, {\"ngram\": \"asoggy opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2549}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The results from additional, more recent samples are not yet publicly available but are reportedly coming soon.\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2665, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The results\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2565}, {\"ngram\": \"additional, more recent samples\", \"from\": 2571, \"to\": 2602}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Testing takes time.\", \"from\": 2666, \"to\": 2685, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Testing\", \"from\": 2666, \"to\": 2673}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 2680, \"to\": 2684}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because bacteria are living organisms, the best way to measure them is to let them grow and replicate, which involves incubating a sample for about 24 hours before analyzing it, Alice Volpitta, the lead water-quality scientist at the advocacy group Blue Water Baltimore, told me.\", \"from\": 2686, \"to\": 2965, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2864, \"end\": 2869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portrayals_of_Alice_in_Wonderland\", \"score\": 0.9974589801686008, \"rank\": 0.002547493061756827, \"text\": \"Alice\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portrayals_of_Alice_in_Wonderland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portrayals_of_Alice_in_Wonderland\"}, {\"begin\": 2935, \"end\": 2945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ocean_Productions\", \"score\": 0.9999999490046334, \"rank\": 5.099502944107237e-08, \"text\": \"Blue Water\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ocean_Productions\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ocean_Productions\"}, {\"begin\": 2946, \"end\": 2955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baltimore\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.796015134741482e-17, \"text\": \"Baltimore\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baltimore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baltimore\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"bacteria\", \"from\": 2694, \"to\": 2702}, {\"ngram\": \"organisms\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2723}, {\"ngram\": \"the best way\", \"from\": 2725, \"to\": 2737}, {\"ngram\": \"a sample\", \"from\": 2815, \"to\": 2823}, {\"ngram\": \"the lead water-quality scientist\", \"from\": 2880, \"to\": 2912}, {\"ngram\": \"the advocacy group\", \"from\": 2916, \"to\": 2934}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once that sample is ready, \\\"it's a look into the past, but it does not tell us what's happening right now,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2966, \"to\": 3083, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that sample\", \"from\": 2971, \"to\": 2982}, {\"ngram\": \"a look\", \"from\": 2999, \"to\": 3005}, {\"ngram\": \"the past\", \"from\": 3011, \"to\": 3019}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3042, \"to\": 3044}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That matters when we are talking about sewage ecosystems, because things can change at the drop of a hat.\\\"\", \"from\": 3084, \"to\": 3191, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sewage ecosystems\", \"from\": 3124, \"to\": 3141}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 3151, \"to\": 3157}, {\"ngram\": \"the drop\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3180}, {\"ngram\": \"a hat\", \"from\": 3184, \"to\": 3189}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The river is probably the cleanest it's been in centuries.\", \"from\": 3195, \"to\": 3253, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The river\", \"from\": 3195, \"to\": 3204}, {\"ngram\": \"centuries\", \"from\": 3243, \"to\": 3252}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well before swimming in the Seine was prohibited about 100 years ago, the river had already earned a reputation as a fetid open sewer.\", \"from\": 3254, \"to\": 3388, \"entities