\"sentence\": \"These tactics can slash the number of spills and the volume of sullied water they introduce, but data are patchy.\", \"from\": 4935, \"to\": 5048, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These tactics\", \"from\": 4935, \"to\": 4948}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 4959, \"to\": 4969}, {\"ngram\": \"spills\", \"from\": 4973, \"to\": 4979}, {\"ngram\": \"the volume\", \"from\": 4984, \"to\": 4994}, {\"ngram\": \"sullied water\", \"from\": 4998, \"to\": 5011}, {\"ngram\": \"data\", \"from\": 5032, \"to\": 5036}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the U.S.,700 municipalitiesstill have these combined pipes; as of two decades ago, they were disgorging850 billion gallonsof fouled water each year, according to the EPA.\", \"from\": 5049, \"to\": 5222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5218, \"end\": 5221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Environmental_Protection_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4871887161463013e-34, \"text\": \"EPA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Environmental_Protection_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Environmental_Protection_Agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the U.S.,700 municipalitiesstill\", \"from\": 5052, \"to\": 5084}, {\"ngram\": \"these combined pipes\", \"from\": 5090, \"to\": 5110}, {\"ngram\": \"disgorging850 billion gallonsof fouled water\", \"from\": 5145, \"to\": 5189}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(The Government Accountability Officehas pushed the EPAto release updated numbers by next year.)\", \"from\": 5223, \"to\": 5319, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Government Accountability Officehas\", \"from\": 5224, \"to\": 5263}, {\"ngram\": \"the EPAto release\", \"from\": 5271, \"to\": 5288}, {\"ngram\": \"updated numbers\", \"from\": 5289, \"to\": 5304}, {\"ngram\": \"next year\", \"from\": 5308, \"to\": 5317}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the meantime, the pipes are doing what they were designed to do.\", \"from\": 5323, \"to\": 5390, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the meantime\", \"from\": 5326, \"to\": 5338}, {\"ngram\": \"the pipes\", \"from\": 5340, \"to\": 5349}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Overflows function as \\\"emergency escape hatches, basically off-ramps for sewage\\\" when a system sees a big influx of water, Volpitta said.\", \"from\": 5391, \"to\": 5528, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"function\", \"from\": 5401, \"to\": 5409}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"emergency escape hatches\", \"from\": 5413, \"to\": 5438}, {\"ngram\": \"basically off-ramps\", \"from\": 5440, \"to\": 5459}, {\"ngram\": \"sewage\", \"from\": 5464, \"to\": 5470}, {\"ngram\": \"a system\", \"from\": 5477, \"to\": 5485}, {\"ngram\": \"a big influx\", \"from\": 5491, \"to\": 5503}, {\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 5507, \"to\": 5512}, {\"ngram\": \"Volpitta\", \"from\": 5514, \"to\": 5522}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tamping down on them helps keep rivers cleaner, but it also creates different hazards: When combined sewers can not spit up water as they previously did (a problem that will only worsen as water levelsinch higherin a wetter, flood-prone world), pipes sometimes belch their contents into streets or basements.\", \"from\": 5529, \"to\": 5837, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"rivers\", \"from\": 5561, \"to\": 5567}, {\"ngram\": \"different hazards\", \"from\": 5597, \"to\": 5614}, {\"ngram\": \"combined sewers\", \"from\": 5621, \"to\": 5636}, {\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 5653, \"to\": 5658}, {\"ngram\": \"a problem\", \"from\": 5683, \"to\": 5692}, {\"ngram\": \"water levelsinch higherin\", \"from\": 5718, \"to\": 5743}, {\"ngram\": \"pipes\", \"from\": 5774, \"to\": 5779}, {\"ngram\": \"their contents\", \"from\": 5796, \"to\": 5810}, {\"ngram\": \"streets\", \"from\": 5816, \"to\": 5823}, {\"ngram\": \"basements\", \"from\": 5827, \"to\": 5836}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of experts' main ideas, beyond lining, replacing, or separating pipes, for addressing these issues is maximizing spongy intercepting ponds, rain gardens,reedbeds, and other green infrastructure to hold or slow water and \\\"minimize the shock of rainfall into the system,\\\" says Franco Montalto, a professor of civil, architectural, and environmental engineering at Drexel University, in Philadelphia.\", \"from\": 5839, \"to\": 6240, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6118, \"end\": 6124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.6821212869804922, \"rank\": 0.4660103204372077, \"text\": \"Franco\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 6125, \"end\": 6133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montalto_delle_Marche\", \"score\": 0.9502184846949333, \"rank\": 0.052295822416117306, \"text\": \"Montalto\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montalto_delle_Marche\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montalto_delle_Marche\"}, {\"begin\": 6205, \"end\": 6222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drexel_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.548594958382974e-22, \"text\": \"Drexel University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drexel_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drexel_University\"}, {\"begin\": 6227, \"end\": 6239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.618938548180873e-19, \"text\": \"Philadelphia\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"experts' main ideas\", \"from\": 5846, \"to\": 5865}, {\"ngram\": \"lining\", \"from\": 5874, \"to\": 5880}, {\"ngram\": \"pipes\", \"from\": 5907, \"to\": 5912}, {\"ngram\": \"these issues\", \"from\": 5929, \"to\": 5941}, {\"ngram\": \"spongy intercepting ponds\", \"from\": 5956, \"to\": 5981}, {\"ngram\": \"rain gardens\", \"from\": 5983, \"to\": 5995}, {\"ngram\": \"reedbeds\", \"from\": 5996, \"to\": 6004}, {\"ngram\": \"other green infrastructure\", \"from\": 6010, \"to\": 6036}, {\"ngram\": \"the shock\", \"from\": 6073, \"to\": 6082}, {\"ngram\": \"rainfall\", \"from\": 6086, \"to\": 6094}, {\"ngram\": \"the system\", \"from\": 6100, \"to\": 6110}, {\"ngram\": \"a professor\", \"from\": 6135, \"to\": 6146}, {\"ngram\": \"civil, architectural, and environmental engineering\", \"from\": 6150, \"to\": 6201}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Philadelphia incentivizes sponginess bycharging for impervious surfaces; bit by bit, Montalto told me, cities could also recontour streets to promote short-term flooding of parks or athletic fields instead of roads that dump into sewers.\", \"from\": 6241, \"to\": 6478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6241, \"end\": 6253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.618938548180873e-19, \"text\": \"Philadelphia\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia\"}, {\"begin\": 6326, \"end\": 6334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montalto_delle_Marche\", \"score\": 0.9502184846949333, \"rank\": 0.052295822416117306, \"text\": \"Montalto\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montalto_delle_Marche\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montalto_delle_Marche\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sponginess\", \"from\": 6267, \"to\": 6277}, {\"ngram\": \"impervious surfaces\", \"from\": 6293, \"to\": 6312}, {\"ngram\": \"bit\", \"from\": 6321, \"to\": 6324}, {\"ngram\": \"cities\", \"from\": 6344, \"to\": 6350}, {\"ngram\": \"streets\", \"from\": 6372, \"to\": 6379}, {\"ngram\": \"short-term flooding\", \"from\": 6391, \"to\": 6410}, {\"ngram\": \"parks\", \"from\": 6414, \"to\": 6419}, {\"ngram\": \"athletic fields\", \"from\": 6423, \"to\": 6438}, {\"ngram\": \"roads\", \"from\": 6450, \"to\": 6455}, {\"ngram\": \"sewers\", \"from\": 6471, \"to\": 6477}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Urban rivers are generally healthier now than they were a few decades ago.\", \"from\": 6482, \"to\": 6556, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Urban rivers\", \"from\": 6482, \"to\": 6494}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But at the moment, \\\"there is no such thing as a risk-free environment in an urban waterway,\\\" Volpitta told me.\", \"from\": 6557, \"to\": 6667, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the moment\", \"from\": 6564, \"to\": 6574}, {\"ngram\": \"no such thing\", \"from\": 6586, \"to\": 6599}, {\"ngram\": \"a risk-free environment\", \"from\": 6603, \"to\": 6626}, {\"ngram\": \"an urban waterway\", \"from\": 6630, \"to\": 6647}, {\"ngram\": \"Volpitta\", \"from\": 6650, \"to\": 6658}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We may see lower bacteria levels but are still exposing people to pathogens and toxins.\\\"\", \"from\": 6668, \"to\": 6757, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"lower bacteria levels\", \"from\": 6680, \"to\": 6701}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 6725, \"to\": 6731}, {\"ngram\": \"pathogens\", \"from\": 6735, \"to\": 6744}, {\"ngram\": \"toxins\", \"from\": 6749, \"to\": 6755}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In New York, for instance, Hudson River Parkshares daily measurementsof water temperature, cloudiness, and more, and worked with several partners to producea public-facing calendarthat indicates likely risks of bacteria connected to sewer overflows.\", \"from\": 6758, \"to\": 7007, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6761, \"end\": 6769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999998030516702, \"rank\": 1.9694843565614114e-07, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"instance\", \"from\": 6775, \"to\": 6783}, {\"ngram\": \"cloudiness\", \"from\": 6849, \"to\": 6859}, {\"ngram\": \"several partners\", \"from\": 6887, \"to\": 6903}, {\"ngram\": \"calendarthat\", \"from\": 6930, \"to\": 6942}, {\"ngram\": \"likely risks\", \"from\": 6953, \"to\": 6965}, {\"ngram\": \"bacteria\", \"from\": 6969, \"to\": 6977}, {\"ngram\": \"sewer\", \"from\": 6991, \"to\": 6996}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(The calendar draws on data gathered a few years ago, on rainy spring days.)\", \"from\": 7008, \"to\": 7084, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The calendar\", \"from\": 7009, \"to\": 7021}, {\"ngram\": \"data\", \"from\": 7031, \"to\": 7035}, {\"ngram\": \"rainy spring days\", \"from\": 7065, \"to\": 7082}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most days in the past year have been low risk; about three dozen have been high (the model does not allow for zero).\", \"from\": 7085, \"to\": 7201, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Most days\", \"from\": 7085, \"to\": 7094}, {\"ngram\": \"the past year\", \"from\": 7098, \"to\": 7111}, {\"ngram\": \"low risk\", \"from\": 7122, \"to\": 7130}, {\"ngram\": \"about three dozen\", \"from\": 7132, \"to\": 7149}, {\"ngram\": \"the model\", \"from\": 7166, \"to\": 7175}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The goal for any river, Volpitta said, is \\\"more swimmable days overall.\\\"\", \"from\": 7202, \"to\": 7274, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The goal\", \"from\": 7202, \"to\": 7210}, {\"ngram\": \"any river\", \"from\": 7215, \"to\": 7224}, {\"ngram\": \"Volpitta\", \"from\": 7226, \"to\": 7234}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Which is, to be fair, what Paris has managed-somedays when the river is swimmable.\", \"from\": 7275, \"to\": 7357, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7302, \"end\": 7307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5840203743392823e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"-somedays\", \"from\": 7319, \"to\": 7328}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 7334, \"to\": 7343}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Claire Robertson, an ecologist and the Oxford Rivers project officer at the England-based environmental charity Thames21, agrees that people belong in rivers.\", \"from\": 7361, \"to\": 7519, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7368, \"end\": 7377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nate_Robertson\", \"score\": 0.5848012763138514, \"rank\": 0.7099825874552865, \"text\": \"Robertson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nate_Robertson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nate_Robertson\"}, {\"begin\": 7400, \"end\": 7406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oxford\", \"score\": 0.9857224612563421, \"rank\": 0.014484339404260534, \"text\": \"Oxford\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oxford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oxford\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an ecologist\", \"from\": 7379, \"to\": 7391}, {\"ngram\": \"the England-based environmental charity\", \"from\": 7433, \"to\": 7472}, {\"ngram\": \"Thames21\", \"from\": 7473, \"to\": 7481}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 7495, \"to\": 7501}, {\"ngram\": \"rivers\", \"from\": 7512, \"to\": 7518}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Vienna's Danube, Munich's Isar, and many rivers squiggling across the U.K. and France all have a long history of hosting swimmers.\", \"from\": 7520, \"to\": 7650, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7520, \"end\": 7526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vienna\", \"score\": 0.9999999999818101, \"rank\": 1.8555206913302067e-11, \"text\": \"Vienna\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vienna\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vienna\"}, {\"begin\": 7529, \"end\": 7535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danube\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5165321470070007e-27, \"text\": \"Danube\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danube\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danube\"}, {\"begin\": 7537, \"end\": 7543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich\", \"score\": 0.9999999960673449, \"rank\": 3.931830973657355e-09, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich\"}, {\"begin\": 7590, \"end\": 7594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.999999731036987, \"rank\": 2.688662004561036e-07, \"text\": \"U.K.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 7599, \"end\": 7605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.551725410253379, \"rank\": 0.8030288536318944, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many rivers\", \"from\": 7556, \"to\": 7567}, {\"ngram\": \"a long history\", \"from\": 7615, \"to\": 7629}, {\"ngram\": \"swimmers\", \"from\": 7641, \"to\": 7649}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Robertson lives on a boat and swims in the Thames several times a week during the warm months-and sometimes during the colder ones too.\", \"from\": 7651, \"to\": 7786, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7651, \"end\": 7660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nate_Robertson\", \"score\": 0.5848012763138514, \"rank\": 0.7099825874552865, \"text\": \"Robertson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nate_Robertson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nate_Robertson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a boat\", \"from\": 7670, \"to\": 7676}, {\"ngram\": \"the Thames\", \"from\": 7690, \"to\": 7700}, {\"ngram\": \"the warm months\", \"from\": 7729, \"to\": 7744}, {\"ngram\": \"the colder ones\", \"from\": 7766, \"to\": 7781}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimming in urban rivers is \\\"absolutely a realistic goal,\\\" she told me.\", \"from\": 7787, \"to\": 7858, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"urban rivers\", \"from\": 7799, \"to\": 7811}, {\"ngram\": \"absolutely a realistic goal\", \"from\": 7816, \"to\": 7843}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Making a river swimmable depends on where you set the threshold and how swimmers think about individual risk tolerance-but planning a dunk for a specific day is tough.\", \"from\": 7859, \"to\": 8026, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a river\", \"from\": 7866, \"to\": 7873}, {\"ngram\": \"the threshold\", \"from\": 7909, \"to\": 7922}, {\"ngram\": \"swimmers\", \"from\": 7931, \"to\": 7939}, {\"ngram\": \"individual risk\", \"from\": 7952, \"to\": 7967}, {\"ngram\": \"tolerance\", \"from\": 7968, \"to\": 7977}, {\"ngram\": \"a dunk\", \"from\": 7991, \"to\": 7997}, {\"ngram\": \"a specific day\", \"from\": 8002, \"to\": 8016}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Good-enough water quality requires planning, funding, patience, and humility in the face of rain-which is unstoppable and utterly indifferent to medal counts.\", \"from\": 8027, \"to\": 8185, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Good-enough water quality\", \"from\": 8027, \"to\": 8052}, {\"ngram\": \"planning\", \"from\": 8062, \"to\": 8070}, {\"ngram\": \"funding\", \"from\": 8072, \"to\": 8079}, {\"ngram\": \"patience\", \"from\": 8081, \"to\": 8089}, {\"ngram\": \"humility\", \"from\": 8095, \"to\": 8103}, {\"ngram\": \"the face\", \"from\": 8107, \"to\": 8115}, {\"ngram\": \"rain\", \"from\": 8119, \"to\": 8123}, {\"ngram\": \"medal counts\", \"from\": 8172, \"to\": 8184}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheAtlantic.com \\u00a92026The Atlantic Monthly Group.\", \"from\": 8193, \"to\": 8241, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8218, \"end\": 8234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlantic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Atlantic Monthly\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlantic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlantic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 8242, \"to\": 8262, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and the GooglePrivacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply\", \"from\": 8264, \"to\": 8352, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This site\", \"from\": 8264, \"to\": 8273}, {\"ngram\": \"reCAPTCHA\", \"from\": 8290, \"to\": 8299}, {\"ngram\": \"the GooglePrivacy PolicyandTerms\", \"from\": 8304, \"to\": 8336}, {\"ngram\": \"Serviceapply\", \"from\": 8340, \"to\": 8352}]}]}"